      <hedline>
        <hl1>Sacred 'Edelweiss'</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Rev James A Smith Jr letter on Kristin Hohenadel's August 27 article on endurance of movie The Sound of Music notes that song Edelweiss is sung as hymn in many churches; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thank you for Kristin Hohenadel's article proving that ''The Sound of Music'' is here to stay [''All Together Now: The Hills Are Still Alive . . .,'' Aug. 27]. If further proof is needed, how about this: there are churches where, with different words, ''Edelweiss'' is sung as a hymn. I have never encouraged this, assuming that the music is copyrighted, but I have heard this sung in a number of different churches. There really is a timeless, enduring quality to that tune and to others in ''The Sound of Music.''</p>
        <p>REV. JAMES A. SMITH JR.  Fort Thomas, Ky.</p>
      </block>
